      <bioghist id="ref7">
         <head>Biographical/Historical Sketch</head>
         <p>Lucille A. Allen was the Dean of Women from 1961-1965.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref8">
         <head>Description of the Collection</head>
         <p>Reports, interviews and correspondence concerning Lucille Allen, Stanford University Dean of Women, and the Women's Council of 1964, consisting of University of women students. Controversy centers around a May, 1964, Women's Council meeting and alleged discussion of "sexual content" of reading materials in freshman English classes.</p>
      </scopecontent>
